<chapter line="1">3. Dvattiṃsākāro</chapter>
<paragraph line="2">Atthi <pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0003" /> imasmiṃ kāye –</paragraph>
<gatha1 line="3">Kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco,</gatha1>
<gatha2 line="4">Maṃsaṃ <alternatives line="3" extra="null" separator="true"><alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">nhāru</alternative><alternative source-abbr="sī. pī." source="sī. pī.">nahāru</alternative><alternative source-abbr="syā. kaṃ." source="syā. kaṃ.">nahārū</alternative></alternatives>  <alternatives line="12" extra="null" separator="false"><alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">aṭṭhi</alternative><alternative source-abbr="syā. kaṃ" source="syā. kaṃ">aṭṭhī</alternative></alternatives>  aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ,</gatha2>
<gatha3 line="5">Hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ,</gatha3>
<gatha2 line="6">Antaṃ antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ matthaluṅgaṃ <note>( ) sabbattha natthi, aṭṭhakathā ca dvattiṃsasaṅkhyā ca manasi kātabbā</note>,</gatha2>
<gatha3 line="7">Pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo,</gatha3>
<gathalast line="8">Assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā <alternatives line="23" extra="null" separator="false"><alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">muttanti</alternative><alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">muttaṃ, matthake matthaluṅganti</alternative></alternatives> .</gathalast>
<centered line="9">Dvattiṃsākāro niṭṭhito.</centered>
